<TITLE> Pabna road link cut off over clashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)Road communications between Pabna and other districts remained suspended on Monday as police, transport workers and students clashed following the death of a college student in a road crash. Pabna assistant superintendent of police Nizamuddin told bdnews24.com that 'Selim', a student of Pabna Edward University College, was injured after he was crushed under the wheels of a bus in the Pabna bypass crossing on Saturday. He was admitted to Rajshahi Medical College Hospital where he succumbed to his injuries on Sunday night, he said. After his death, the college students took to streets that night. They staged demonstrations at around 10am on Monday and damaged some 15-16 vehicles and five to six shops in front of the college. They also clashed with transport workers and the police. Additional district magistrate Imam Uddin Kabir said riot police were deployed at different points of the town. bdn
